{
  "texts": [
    "Adaptability to FeedbackAdaptability to feedback, a crucial aspect of model performance, was systematically evaluated by introducing modifications based on initial outputs and assessing subsequent improvements.",
    "As depicted in Figure 4, Mistral 7B and TripoSR showed outstanding adaptability, swiftly incorporating feedback to refine both their decision-making processes and the clarity of their explanations.",
    "This rapid adjustment highlights their advanced learning architectures capable of dynamic evolution based on new information.",
    "GemMoE-Beta-1 and Llama-2-7b exhibited moderate adaptability, demonstrating tangible improvements over time, albeit at a more gradual pace.",
    "This suggests a solid but less flexible framework for integrating iterative feedback."
  ]
}